Edit: In reply to managements comment. We used to live at a sister property to this complex. We transfered our lease to Parkside for the job opportunities. We were led to believe that we would be having the exact same lease since both properties were owned by the same person and managed by Lincoln. You should avoid Parkside at all costs. They take advantage of the pandemic and people losing jobs. My husband and I moved to Parkside for work. Because of the Pandemic, they have revoked the ability to transfer to sister properties. This place is taking advantage of those being affected by Covid. This is such a bad company and apartment. We asked if we could set up a payment plan, and Ty in Leasing said he would ask corporate and ghosted us. I cannot voice how horrible this complex is. If you move here. reviews.author: Z C (Chucky2sRevenge)
reviews.text: You might think this complex looks nice and is in a good area, but once you pull into it you'll notice the gates do not work.  Anyone can drive in and through the complex, despite them advertising as a private parking lot.  This has been the case since Avenue 5 has purchased the property back in June 2021.  They have not been able to get trash cleanup under control.  They have not fixed issues with the mail room and now they keep YOUR packages in their office.  This makes it super inconvenient to get your mail.  The dog park is sad and often taken over by the same groups of people with hostile dogs that force you to leave.  The parking garage is a danger because this property has no speed bumps or mirrors or signage.  People speed all the time through here.  You cannot smoke inside the property yet there are no smoking designated areas outside.  There has been zero improvements made and in fact, many amenities are now worthless or not working here. Lastly, and perhaps most concerning, is the issue with the complex's gates. They are frequently broken and remain open, allowing free access to the property. This lack of security has directly resulted in thefts in the complex. The management has shown little urgency or concern in addressing this significant safety issue.

Furthermore, the customer service at Nexus East is deplorable. The management lacks accountability and has shown little to no interest in resolving the issues we have brought to their attention. Requests and complaints seem to fall on deaf ears, leaving us feeling ignored and undervalued as residents.

In conclusion, living at Nexus East Apartment Complex has been a frustrating and disappointing experience. The management's lack of regard for tenant rights, false advertisement of amenities, and poor customer service have made my stay here an ordeal. I strongly advise potential renters to consider these issues before choosing to live at Nexus East.

Hopefully the management company will follow up.
